King's Day (birthday of King WILLEM-ALEXANDER), 27 April (1967);
note - King's or Queen's Day are observed on the ruling monarch's
birthday; celebrated on 26 April if 27 April is a Sunday

defense is the responsibility of the Kingdom of the Netherlands;
the Dutch Government controls foreign and defense policy; the Dutch
Caribbean Coast Guard (DCCG) provides maritime security (2022)
